        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:47PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Braddyville, or 13 miles northwest of Maryville, moving northeast at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hopkins, Braddyville, and Clearmont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
northwestern Missouri.</instruction>
